snippet.textDisplay: I think it was almost certainly the pandemic that caused Chrome OS market share to surge.  Just about every school system went to remote instruction last year and needed to purchase computers for students to use at home.  Chromebooks were already used extensively in education and generally cost less than Mac and Windows machines.  On top of that many school districts, including NYC public schools used google classroom for remote instruction.  It hardly seems surprising there was a surge in demand for chrome books.
